##A great revival of the National Land Market

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

Reporter: Fu Lin Lin

“

Now it's gambling to take the land.

”

Although the project of housing enterprises has not yet started, but in the land market around, the competition of housing enterprises has already begun.

On February 14, Beijing held its second Earth auction of the year of the rat, with three lots in Haidian District and Changping District selling for 19.68 billion yuan. And just three days ago, Beijing has just carried out the first land auction after the festival, three pieces of land sold 8 billion yuan, the same fierce competition between real estate enterprises.

Zhang Dawei, chief analyst at the Real Estate Research Institute in Central Plain, said: "recently, those who dare to take the land are actually gambling. If the epidemic can be alleviated quickly, they must be bottom-feeders who have obtained high-quality land at the base price and are overtaking at the corners. But if the epidemic continues, then it is likely to be a fall into the mire. ". "

Those who dare to actively take the current stage of the real estate enterprises, apparently the land market and the future has an optimistic forecast, of course, there are also real estate enterprises will be cautious. In the current market environment, housing enterprises between the judgment of the future has been a huge difference.

Over the past decade of several rounds of regulatory cycle, the courage to gamble real estate enterprises, if the market can be accurate, often get a huge return. But this time, in the strict regulation of the industry, "housing does not speculation" will not change the main tone of the background, high-stakes housing enterprises can go to the end, it is still a big question mark.

For the cash-strapped soes, they see this as a good opportunity to grab land.

"although affected by the epidemic, it has to be said that this is the best time in the last four or five years for Beijing to seize land and for real estate enterprises to enter the city, " an executive at a state-owned enterprise in Beijing told interface news.

Although the epidemic is serious, but can not stop all over the Internet to continue to sell land. In addition to Beijing, major cities across the country also set off a heat wave. Guangzhou, Hangzhou, Nanjing, Chengdu, Fuzhou, Wenzhou and other places have begun after the first land sale. One of Wenzhou Land Auction 9 hours, bidding more than 400 rounds to determine the winner.

Shanghai also recently put up a huge piece of land -- Foshan -- consisting of 28 pieces of land, the West Bank financial port of Ben Giang, Xuhui District, with a starting price of 31.02 billion yuan. If it goes through, it will probably break the record of the total land price in China.

Orient Securities said in a report, with the second half of 2019 land premium rate continued to decline, this year is expected to have a good opportunity to cover positions.

According to the situation of the last two land auctions in Beijing, the three land lots on February 11 were won by the first, China Resources and China Communications, and Beijing Energy. On February 14, the land lots were won by the first + China resources + living in total + China Communications, Green City, first + living in total + construction. It is clear that property companies, which have the status of state owned enterprises, are in the vanguard.

Beijing real estate commentator Zeron said that due to Beijing land auction total price threshold is high, the beginning of the year to supply more land, a large number of competitive housing homogenized product inventory pressure, and affected by the epidemic, part of the scale, high leverage, fast turnover, high debt to the current stage of housing enterprises will be more cautious, of course, behind the cash flow is a rigid factor.

To support normal economic development under the epidemic, liquidity in financial markets has been released recently.

On February 3, the central bank launched a 1.2 trillion yuan reverse repurchase operation in the open market. The overall liquidity of the banking system was 900 billion yuan more than in the same period last year, the cumulative release of liquidity reached 1.7 trillion yuan, which is equivalent to a 1% reduction in reserve requirements. Most people in the real estate industry do not rule out the possibility of easy money eventually flowing into the real estate market.

"The central bank is definitely good for real estate, but it is mainly good for large-scale real estate companies, " the state-owned company executive told Imew. "Small and medium-sized enterprises will have a worse living environment. From a financing point of view, last year's situation was not good. Now, of course, it is worse. "

Zhang Peng, the president of contemporary real estate, said that the financing costs of small and medium sized housing enterprises are relatively higher, the deactivation cycle is longer, the capital pressure is greater than that of state owned enterprises and large head enterprises, and the number of mergers and acquisitions between enterprises will increase to a certain extent in the whole year, industry concentration is expected to increase further.

Contemporary real estate sales in 2019 about 36.2 billion yuan, the national ranking of about 80 housing enterprises, is among the small and medium-sized housing enterprises.

Recently, the real estate companies have also generally increased the strength of foreign financing, although the interest rate of dollar debt has dropped, but for small and medium-sized enterprises, financing costs remain high.

Among the latest US dollar debt issues in February, Zhongliang and Rongsheng each paid more than 8 per cent, while Zhejiang Fangqi Jiayuan international paid 13.75 per cent on a $60m senior note.

An employee of a trust also told interface news, "At present, we do not do financing for small housing enterprises, the risk is relatively large, before we only do the first 50 housing enterprises, after the expansion will do the first 100, but still depends on the project conditions and wind control measures. "

Financing side of the general will also be directly reflected in the land auction market.

Bai Yanjun, general manager of the enterprise and business department of the Middle Finger Research Institute, said that at present, for housing enterprises with relatively healthy financial conditions, it is a good time to take the land, targeting some large state-owned enterprises as well as enterprises with relatively abundant funds, their ability to cross the cycle is relatively strong, suggesting that these enterprises in the current appropriate active investment in priority second-tier cities, including affected by the city.

For enterprises under short-term financial pressure, it is recommended to avoid cities that are heavily affected by the epidemic in the short term, as the liquidity of sales proceeds in these cities will be weaker, and also avoid some third-and fourth-tier cities, but more layout of the liquidity of the relatively strong first-and second-tier cities.

At present, the epidemic has already had an impact on the macro-economy. Zhongshan Securities Analysis believes that due to major changes in the industrial structure, the contribution of consumption to economic growth has increased significantly at present, in particular, the impact on the service sector, which is closely related to offline consumption, has been even greater. Since the end of January 2020, the government has adopted more stringent measures in the prevention and control of the epidemic, especially extending the Spring Festival holiday and postponing the resumption of work by enterprises, the impact on industrial production is relatively large.

At present, the real estate market has entered the era of stock, and the probability of a major relaxation of real estate regulation at this stage is low, so the role of real estate in pulling the economy is limited; China is currently in an economic downturn cycle, it is possible that the subsequent economic rebound will be weaker than during SARS.

And in the real estate sector, affected by the epidemic, projects across the country are in a state of shutdown. Evergrande alone has 1,246 projects that have been shut down. At present, there is still no clear notification of the resumption of projects around the country. After January, fuzhou, Ganzhou, Yichang, Guangzhou, Zhanjiang, Tengchong City, Kunming, Nanjing, Xiamen and other cities have issued notices requiring companies to close sales offices. And from the January sales data of listed housing enterprises, basically in a downward trend.

According to the survey data of the all-union Real Estate Chamber of Commerce, enterprises in the first half of 2020 to deliver projects accounted for 30%-50% of the total number of projects delivered in the whole year, the survey of 72 enterprises, 46 housing enterprises mainly affected by small and medium enterprises value of more than 440 billion yuan; 26 industrial chain enterprises, affected by the shutdown of inventory more than 4 billion yuan; a typical housing enterprise capital shortfall will reach 10-11 billion yuan a month, the first half of the money or only enough to maintain three months of operation.

But regarding the aftermarket, many housing enterprises interviewees have expressed the obvious confidence.

"At present, Beijing has a large and very dense land supply, " said the state-owned executive. "judging from the enthusiasm and bidding of the land auction companies, I feel we are all very confident. "

Most people judge that the need to buy houses in the epidemic has not disappeared, in the end of the epidemic, the real estate market will appear a wave of growth. In addition, in the policy, especially to ease the pressure on corporate funds, the local also loosened up.

Up to now, Jinan, Xi'an, Hangzhou, Shanghai, Tianjin, Wuxi, Nanchang, Nanjing and other cities have introduced new land policies to deal with the epidemic situation. Some cities have made it clear that land payment can be applied for extension or payment by installments.

On February 12, policies and measures to combat the epidemic and stabilize the economy were introduced overnight in Wuxi and Xi'an, before this, Hebei, Tianjin, Chongqing, Zhejiang, Shanghai, Nanchang and other 10 provinces and cities have also introduced a real estate industry, especially real estate enterprises staged bail-out new policies.

"from a national perspective, if Hubei can control the epidemic in February and combine policies such as expected interest rate cuts, the market will recover quickly, " Zhang said. "there may even be a significant resurgence of Xiaoyangchun. "

And Zeron said: "If everyone is confident that this outbreak will be contained in the short term at the pace of a few months and the level one response will be unwound, then the hardest thing is not to get the ground now, but to get the project a few months ago. Just now to take the land, the opening point may be just in time to catch up with all the normal property market big spring."

But the timing of the market still depends on when the epidemic ends, the state-owned executives said, predicting a medium-sized market in Beijing in the second half of the year.
